This paper proposes a novel method for knowledge transfer in deep learning applications, which is a common topic in the machine learning community. The paper specifically focuses on image datasets, which suggests that it may fall under the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. The use of an adversarial generator also suggests a potential connection to the generative adversarial networks (GANs) sub-category (cs.LG). The paper also discusses the use of a metric to quantify belief matching, which could be related to natural language processing (cs.CL) or artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Finally, the paper's focus on data privacy and the use of no data suggests a potential connection to the neural privacy (cs.NE) sub-category. Overall, the most likely sub-categories are cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.CL, and cs.NE, in that order.
